## New Concepts Learned

| Concept | What it means |
|---------|-------------|
| **Component Architecture** | Breaking a complex UI into small, focused, reusable pieces — each with one job |
| **CSS Custom Properties** | Variables like `--vscode-bg: #1e1e1e` that you reference with `var(--vscode-bg)` — one change updates everywhere |
| **Design Tokens** | A standardized way of storing design values (colors, sizes, fonts) as variables |
| **Recursive Components** | A component that renders itself — TreeItem renders more TreeItems for nested folders |
| **React Fragments `<>...</>`** | Group multiple elements without adding an extra DOM wrapper |
| **`e.stopPropagation()`** | Prevents a click event from bubbling up to parent elements |
| **`useCallback`** | Memoizes a function so it's not recreated on every render — performance optimization |
| **`return null`** | Makes a component render nothing — used to hide the sidebar |
| **Container/Content Pattern** | Sidebar (container) delegates to FileExplorer/SearchPanel (content) |
| **Forward-Compatible Design** | Building UI for features you know are coming (like the Recent section in WelcomeTab) |
| **Dynamic Component Rendering** | Storing components in variables/arrays and rendering them with `<item.icon />` |
| **Tab Management** | Open, close, switch between tabs using React state — mimicking VS Code's tab system |

