**Test the full flow:**

1. Open `http://localhost:5173` — you should see the Welcome page
2. Click **"Create Room..."** — you should be redirected to `/room/<some-uuid>`
3. The editor opens with a blank file. Type something like "Hello from Room A!"
4. **Copy the URL** from the address bar (e.g., `http://localhost:5173/room/abc-123`)
5. Open a **new browser tab** and paste that URL
6. You should see **"Hello from Room A!"** already there — the code syncs!
7. Type in the second tab → it appears in the first tab instantly
8. Now go back to the first tab and click the home icon or navigate to `http://localhost:5173`
9. Click **"Create Room..."** again — you get a DIFFERENT room with a DIFFERENT UUID
10. The new room is empty — completely isolated from the first room!

> **What to verify:**
> - ✅ Creating a room generates a unique URL
> - ✅ Sharing the URL connects both users to the same room
> - ✅ Different rooms have completely independent code
> - ✅ The status bar shows "Live" when connected
> - ✅ Navigating back to `/` disconnects from the room

