## How the Data Flows Now (The Full Picture)

```
User A clicks "Create Room" on the Welcome page
        │
        ▼
WelcomePage generates UUID: "abc-123-def"
        │
        ▼
navigate('/room/abc-123-def')
        │
        ▼
React Router matches /room/:roomId → renders <RoomPage />
        │
        ▼
RoomPage calls useParams() → roomId = "abc-123-def"
        │
        ▼
RoomPage calls getRoom("abc-123-def")
        │
        ├─ Creates new Y.Doc
        ├─ Creates Y.Text named 'monaco'
        └─ Creates WebsocketProvider → connects to ws://localhost:1234
                                        with room name "abc-123-def"
        │
        ▼
User A types "Hello!" in the editor
        │
        ▼
MonacoBinding → updates Y.Text → WebsocketProvider sends to server
        │
        ▼
Yjs server stores the update in room "abc-123-def"

        === Meanwhile, User B receives the URL ===

User B opens http://localhost:5173/room/abc-123-def
        │
        ▼
React Router → RoomPage → useParams() → roomId = "abc-123-def"
        │
        ▼
getRoom("abc-123-def") → creates Y.Doc + provider for "abc-123-def"
        │
        ▼
WebsocketProvider connects to ws://localhost:1234 room "abc-123-def"
        │
        ▼
Server sends current state of room "abc-123-def" to User B
        │
        ▼
User B's Y.Text receives "Hello!"
        │
        ▼
MonacoBinding updates User B's Monaco Editor
        │
        ▼
User B sees "Hello!" ✅  Real-time collaboration is live!
```

